      "commit": {
        "parents": [
          {
            "commit": "d36f00b3b7c977acf1a092d188535d34d079c57a",
            "subject": "LU-6722 ldiskfs: fix credits at ldiskfs_delete_inode"
          }
        ],
        "author": {
          "name": "Patrick Farrell",
          "email": "paf@cray.com",
          "date": "2016-04-05 15:48:57.000000000",
          "tz": -300
        },
        "committer": {
          "name": "Oleg Drokin",
          "email": "oleg.drokin@intel.com",
          "date": "2016-05-02 23:57:54.000000000",
          "tz": 0
        },
        "subject": "LU-7981 llite: take trunc_sem only at vvp layer",
        "message": "LU-7981 llite: take trunc_sem only at vvp layer\n\nThe lli_trunc_sem is taken in 'read' mode in both\nll_page_mkwrite and vvp_io_fault_start. This can lead to a\ndeadlock with another thread which asks for the semaphore\nin write mode between thse two read calls.\n\nSince all users of lli_trunc_sem are in the vvp layer, we\ncan satisfy the requirement to exclude truncate by taking\nthe semaphore only in vvp_io_fault_start.\n\nSigned-off-by: Patrick Farrell <paf@cray.com>\nChange-Id: I7341d179f550835ccebfb1bb2d90260c1d5d0ff8\nReviewed-on: http://review.whamcloud.com/19315\nTested-by: Jenkins\nReviewed-by: Jinshan Xiong <jinshan.xiong@intel.com>\nTested-by: Maloo <hpdd-maloo@intel.com>\nReviewed-by: Andriy Skulsyh\nReviewed-by: Oleg Drokin <oleg.drokin@intel.com>\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
  "requirements": [],
  "submit_records": []
}